benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from payment

covered: Valid deletion scenarios fully covered (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC20)
Authorization/Authentication handling tested (TC11 missing header -> 400, TC12 invalid token -> 401)
Header usage and variation (TC03 with optional headers),
Validation and security edge cases covered (TC08 invalid paymentId format, TC13 malformed customField, TC16 mixed valid/invalid, TC17 XSS header, TC18 SQL injection, TC19 slow/degraded system)
Large payload and performance coverage (TC06 with 100 fields, TC15 with 1000 fields, TC19 performance)
Integration/dependencies scenarios covered (TC21 audit log available, TC22 audit log unavailable)
Regression and backward compatibility covered (TC20 regression test, TC23 legacy client)
Non-existent resource handling (TC09 non-existent payment, TC10 non-existent customField IDs)
gaps: Concurrency testing: no explicit race condition/concurrent deletion scenarios
Soft delete semantics: no explicit soft-delete behavior tested
Pagination specifics for delete results: not explicitly tested (though large field counts are covered)
recommendations: Add explicit concurrency/race-condition tests for DELETE operations
Add tests around soft-delete semantics if applicable to the domain
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests for DOS-prevention scenarios
Add caching header validation (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses
If pagination for delete flows is a future concern, add dedicated pagination tests; otherwise document its inapplicability
Extend security testing with additional edge cases (e.g., header encoding, extremely long headers)
